frameDefinitions: An Agent acts in such a way as to give the incorrect impression to observers that a particular State_of_affairs holds.
Short selling, a common financial market concept, involves an Intermediary selling Assets to the Market, having borrowed these Assets from a (generally implicit) Lender.
A Figure is located essentially at the same location as a Ground, which is viewed as point-like, or having no important internal or external structure.
An Agent actively maintains or improves their level of phyiscal fitness.
An Agent enacts an Action that is intended to be performed again at one or more later Occasions.
An Agent performs an Action incorrectly.
frameExamples: Jordan <t>feigned</t> a love of jazz music to get her phone number .
He was <t>selling</t> <t>short</t> shares from his brother's company on the NASDAQ and he made a fortune.
I <t>practiced</t> my song for the play.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who acts in a misleading way to create the impression that a <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> holds.
This is the entity which is copied. With verbs it is frequently expressed as an NP Object: Pat <t>falsified</t> <fex name='Original'>the papers</fex>.
The Copy produced by the Creator most commonly occurs as the External Argument of a predicative use of an adjective or noun target: <fex name='Copy'>The painting</fex> is a <t>fake</t>.
The <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> is a an event, a state, or a property that the <fen>Agent</fen> wants others to believe have occurred or hold.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> feigns something.
The place in which the <fen>Agent</fen> feigns something.
The original owner and soon to be <fen>Lender</fen> of the <fen>Assets</fen>.
The financial <fen>Assets</fen> being traded.
The entity that is the borrower to the <fen>Lender</fen> and the seller and later repurchaser to the <fen>Market</fen>.
The aggregate selling place of many types of financial stocks, bond, securities, etc. The <fen>Market</fen> is also a metonym for the people who buy the <fen>Assets</fen>.
This role identifies the time at which the <fen>Intermediary</fen> engages in short selling.
This role identifies the place at which the short selling occurs.
The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location. The <fen>Figure</fen> can be an entity or an event.
The period of time during which the locative relation between <fen>Figure</fen> and <fen>Ground</fen> obtains.
The person who is trying to improve or maintain their physical fitness.
The time that the <fen>Agent</fen> exercises.
The location of the Agent while exercising.
This role identifies the <fen>Action</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> performs intentionally in order to prepare for a later <fen>Occasion</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> performs the <fen>Action</fen> in preparation for later performances of the same type.
The later enactment or enactments that the <fen>Agent</fen> expects to perform. Note that the <fen>Agent</fen> does not have to have specific <fen>Occasion</fen>s in mind.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> practices.
This role identifies the place where the practicing occurs.
The <fen>Agent</fen> performs an action incorrectly.
<fen>Patient</fen> is the entity affected by the <fen>Agent</fen>'s bungling of an <fen>Action</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Action</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> performs incorrectly.
The type of action that the <fen>Agent</fen> habitually bungles.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the bungling occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the bungling occurs.
listRoleExamples: A year after <fex>Audrey Seiler</fex> faked her own kidnapping while at college in Wisconsin, her lawyer says she's getting help and paying restitution.
A college student who staged <fex>her own disappearance</fex> last month will try to reach a plea agreement and avoid trial on charges she obstructed officers.
He was at my shop <fex>on Friday</fex>.
<fex>The manager</fex> exercises before and after work.
Little Dieter practiced <fex>playing the piano</fex> all day.
<fex>For our brother's wedding</fex> we had to rehearse the dinner twenty times.
Our band practices <fex>on the football field</fex>.
The Austro-Hungarian Empire had a long history of <fex>military</fex> screw-ups.
